items.sentence: I don't know what Tom wants to eat for dinner.
I don't like the fact that Tom is dating Mary.
I don't remember Tom's younger brother's name.
I don't think Tom will permit Mary to do that.
I don't think Tom would let me borrow his car.
I'd like to go to Tom's house and talk to him.
I'm giving Tom a new bicycle for his birthday.
Next week, Tom is going to Boston on business.
I think Tom and I might've poisoned ourselves.
I think Tom and I should do that by ourselves.
